Hermeticore, the planet where the story "[[Heart Of Foromor\|Heart Of Foromor]]" passes, was forged by [[Hermeticore/Pathos\|Pathos]], a god, which has a peculiar hobby of creating worlds and providing them with all the stepping stones to evolution, and then wreaking havoc between their population to see how they adapt. With the goal of creating an "immortal" world.

Magic in Hermeticore exudes from the [[Hermeticore/Magic/Planet core\|Planet core]], it escapes through [[Hermeticore/Magic/Divergent Boundaries\|Divergent Boundaries]], Volcanoes, and other such things. This means volcanic lands don't just fertilize the plants, it enchants them. Also that some parts of the ocean are pretty dangerous, containing high amounts of mana coming from seeps of mana.

The reason behind it, is that Pathos wanted to create a self sustainable species, that did not *need* to pray to him or any other gods for power or magic. Using the flowing [[Hermeticore/Magic/Mana\|Mana]] and redirecting it for their own needs.

This meant that their [[Hermeticore/Magic/Magic System\|Magic System]] required much more studying than ones where the casters pray for gods and such. 

At the start of Hermeticore's lifespan, [[Hermeticore/Pathos\|Pathos]] created most living beings on the planet, he also made humans all equal, but due to the [[Hermeticore/Magic/Planet core\|Planet core]] being made of pure mana, volatile and ever changing, it corrupted any living beings exposed to it for too long.

This created different [[Hermeticore/Heritages\|Heritages]]. Among other creatures and monsters.

It is important to note that Hermeticore has been in contact with other dimensions such as [[Hermeticore/The Nether\|The Nether]] and [[Hermeticore/The Void\|The Void]]. Dimensions that often aim to take over worlds that come in contact with them, something Pathos predicted, hence why he gave this world such strong sources of power.
